</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[189,1399,1451,1727]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,574,1451,1477]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collis" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Floccocheila">
<emphasis box="[189,305,1451,1477]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[327,486,1451,1477]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Floccocheila</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[508,574,1451,1477]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">collis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[586,683,1451,1477]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from all known members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov" authorityYear="2002" box="[1150,1309,1451,1477]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Floccocheila">
<emphasis box="[1150,1309,1451,1477]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Floccocheila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the combination of the following characters: basoflagellomere brownish-orange, face without pilosity, scutum yellowish pilose with a broad transverse band of black pilosity of different lengths at level of wing bases, scutellum yellowish pilose with an area of black pilosity centrally, and pleura and abdomen densely yellow pilose. 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[451,680,1594,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collis" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Floccocheila">
<emphasis box="[451,563,1594,1620]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[580,602,1594,1619]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">F.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[617,680,1594,1620]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">collis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[686,774,1594,1620]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to the Nepalese species 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[1164,1398,1594,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="illustratoides" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Floccocheila">
<emphasis box="[1164,1190,1594,1620]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1207,1230,1594,1619]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">F.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1244,1398,1594,1620]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">illustratoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[189,281,1630,1656]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[340,590,1629,1656]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leucozonoides" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Floccocheila">
<emphasis box="[340,367,1630,1656]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[384,406,1630,1655]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">F.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[424,590,1629,1655]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">leucozonoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[598,692,1630,1656]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, from which it differs in having tergite III with only yellow pilosity (vs tergite III laterally with black pilosity in 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[823,1063,1665,1692]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="illustratoides" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Floccocheila">
<emphasis box="[823,850,1666,1692]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[867,889,1666,1691]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">F.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[907,1063,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">illustratoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1071,1164,1666,1692]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and black pilose in 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[190,438,1701,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leucozonoides" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Floccocheila">
<emphasis box="[190,217,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[233,255,1702,1727]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">F.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[272,438,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">leucozonoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[445,540,1701,1727]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,892,1767,1840]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="etymology">
