<paragraph blockId="26.[189,892,1814,1840]" box="[189,892,1814,1840]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
The specific epithet is from the Latin ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[639,703,1814,1840]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collis">
<emphasis box="[639,703,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">collis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ meaning ‘hill’.
</paragraph>
